title: Grace Harlowe's Plebe Year at High School
creator: Jessie Graham Flower
description: LibriVox recording of Grace Harlowe's Plebe Year at High School, by Jessie Graham Flower. Read by Christine Blachford. This delightful book tells about a group of smart youths who get up to some wonderful adventures together - and save one another from troubles. The unofficial leader of the group is Grace Harlowe, the title character. When Anne Pierson comes to the class at the beginning of the year, they decide to take her under their wing. Anne has a lot of troubles at home, but will true friends make her happy? (Summary by Stav Nisser) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B audiobook of complete book
subject: librivox; audiobook; fiction; teen; youth; adolescent
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: Delightful story and beautifully read. Thoroughly enjoyable. I love coming across these delightful stories which - because they're so old - I would never have found on the shelves at the local library. Thanks so much librivox
